<TITLE> 4 arrested over Benapole fair blast </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Jessore, Apr 29 (bdnews24.com)  Police have detained four suspects on Thursday for the bombing at Benapole's Baishakhi Fair. They are Bhaberberh village residents Israfil, 25, Liton, 30, Firoz, 25, and Shohag, 22, of Boro Achra village. "The four were arrested on suspicion of being involved in the bombing," Benapole port police sub-inspector Ali Akbar told journalists. He said the administration shut down the fair following the bombing and the traders had removed their stalls from the spot. One person was killed and eight others injured when the bomb blasted at the Baishakhi fair in Benapole around 10pm on Wednesday. The dead was identified as Zia, 20, son of Shamsuzzoha from Sadipur village in Benapole. bdn
